<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-723-397  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 723 397.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 14 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Northwest cellular service to be linked to Canada. (McCawCellular)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   McCaw Cellular Inc. (Services).andO;Topic:     Cellular radioCommunications Service SuppliersTelecommunications ServicesTelephone CompaniesCanada.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NORTHWEST CELLULAR SERVICE TO BE LINKED TO CANADA 12/14/90 KIRKLAND,WASHINGTON, U.S.A., 1990 DEC 14 (NB) -- McCaw Cellular is upgrading itsswitching system to provide seamless coverage from the Pacific Northwest tothe whole of Canada.andP;  Callers in Washington along I-90 or I-5 will soon beable to make and receive calls regardless of where they are at any giventime, without having to use cumbersome special access codes or roamingnumbers.andM;The plan can be seen as the harbinger for McCaw's goal of creating a completenationwide cellular network.andP;  McCaw paid $1.5 billion to acquire LinBroadcasting in a bidding war with BellSouth to become the main beneficiaryof such a network.andM;Initially, system conversion in Seattle, Portland and Spokane creates aseamless network extending into British Columbia.andP;  The new network, however,will soon expand throughout Canada, where McCaw Cellular has reached anagreement with Rogers Cantel of Canada to integrate the two systems.andP;  Cantelhas already developed a nationwide network that is compatible with the newCellular One switch to be installed in Seattle.andM;By virtue of this arrangement, a Cellular One customer based in Seattle whohappens to be in Montreal, for example, will be reached by dialing theSeattle telephone number and it will ring in Montreal without using anyroaming or access codes.andM;The new switches and cell sites are digital-ready in anticipation of aconversion to a fully digital cellular network.andP;  Because a digital systemspeeds transmissions while allowing the network to handle many more calls,the new network will also allow for an additional range of services -- suchas data transmission via computer and fax.andM;An industry spokesman said that, for the U.S., nationwide call delivery is&quot;only a year away.andP;  I'll be able to take my Washington-based phone to Chicagoand my Washington number will find me there.andP;  We've already validated thetechnology.&quot;andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19901214/Press Contact: McCaw Cellular, Bob Ratliffe,206/828-8685)</TEXT></DOC>